The paper introduces two novel non-parametric statistical hypothesis tests that are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The first test, the relative test of dependency, can be applied to problems in machine learning, natural language processing, and bioinformatics, among others. The second test, the relative test of similarity, is useful in model comparison problems in deep generative models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also uses statistical methods and concepts, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
